variables.name: BIG_ENDIAN
variables.comment:
* Constant denoting big-endian byte order.  In this order, the bytes of a
     * multibyte value are ordered from most significant to least significant.

variables.name: LITTLE_ENDIAN
variables.comment:
* Constant denoting little-endian byte order.  In this order, the bytes of
     * a multibyte value are ordered from least significant to most
     * significant.

variables.name: NATIVE_ORDER
variables.comment: must be initialized after BIG_ENDIAN and LITTLE_ENDIAN.

methods.name: public static ByteOrder nativeOrder()
methods.comment:
* Retrieves the native byte order of the underlying platform. * *

This method is defined so that performance-sensitive Java code can * allocate direct buffers with the same byte order as the hardware. * Native code libraries are often more efficient when such buffers are * used.

* * @return The native byte order of the hardware upon which this Java * virtual machine is running

methods.name: public String toString()
methods.comment:
* Constructs a string describing this object. * *

This method returns the string * {@code "BIG_ENDIAN"} for {@link #BIG_ENDIAN} and * {@code "LITTLE_ENDIAN"} for {@link #LITTLE_ENDIAN}. * * @return The specified string
